A. Saltelli
dcterms:description: Ishigami's function includes three independent inputs following a uniform distribution on [-π, π], defined as f(x) = sin(x1) + 7 sin^2(x2) + 0.1x3^4 sin(x1). It is used for sensitivity analysis.
dcterms:title: Ishigami's function

dcterms:creator: T. Homma
A. Saltelli
dcterms:description: Sobol's g-function includes ten independent inputs following a uniform distribution on [0, 1], defined as f(x) = product from j=1 to d of |4xj - 2| + aj / (1 + aj). It is used for sensitivity analysis.
dcterms:title: Sobol's g-function
